csFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529961\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 03, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mko1665702747232.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mko1665702747232.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mko1665702747232.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mko1665702747232\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Returning Standalone\n      On-Premises Served Licenses </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">If you have a standalone on-premises served license that is no longer required, you\n      can return it using the license revocation tool to disable the license file. </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"mko1665702747232__context_w1520ab1b5b1_w1521ab1b5_w1522ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mko1665702747232__p_d67085e1_d67086e1_d67087e1\">To revoke a license, you will need the Revocation Tool provided in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common/bin</span> directory of your Uniface installation as well as in the RMS installation package. This is a Java-based tool that can be run on any platform.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mko1665702747232__p_d67097e1_d67098e1_d67099e1\">To revoke a license:</p>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mko1665702747232__li_d29702e1_d29703e1_d29704e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"mko1665702747232__p_d67100e1_d67101e1_d67102e1\">Open the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common/bin</span> directory and double-click the <span class=\"ph filepath\">Sentinel RMS Revocation Tool.jar</span> file.\n You can also run the tool from the command line using the command:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">C:/Program Files/Uniface/Uniface 10/common/jre/bin/java.exe\" –jar “Sentinel RMS Revocation Tool.jar”</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"mko1665702747232__note_w1523ab1b5b3b1b3b3_w1524ab1b5b3b1b3_w1525ab1b5b3b1_w1526ab1b5b3_w1527ab1b5_w1528ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> \n                        Update the file path to match your Uniface installation.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mko1665702747232__li_d29705e1_d29706e1_d29707e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">When prompted, choose between:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mko1665702747232__li_d29708e1_d29709e1_d29710e1\">Revoke Immediately—perform instant revocation\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mko1665702747232__li_d29711e1_d29712e1_d29713e1\">Manual Revoke—perform a step-by-step process for revocation\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mko1665702747232__li_d29714e1_d29715e1_d29716e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"mko1665702747232__p_d67103e1_d67104e1_d67105e1\">If you select <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Revoke Immediately</span>, enter your user input values (Product Key, Entitlement ID, or Username) and license information (Activation ID, License File, or License String) when prompted.\n The complete revocation is performed immediately and revocation related records are automatically updated on the EMS portal.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mko1665702747232__li_d29717e1_d29718e1_d29719e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you select <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Manual Revoke</span>, on the Generate Permission Ticket screen, enter your login and license information and click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Generate</span>. This generates a permission ticket.\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"mko1665702747232__li_d29720e1_d29721e1_d29722e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">On the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Perform Revocation</span> screen, provide the permission ticket and click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Revoke</span>.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"mko1665702747232__li_d29723e1_d29724e1_d29725e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Choose a file name and location to save the generated revocation ticket.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"mko1665702747232__li_d29726e1_d29727e1_d29728e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">On the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Upload Revocation Ticket</span> screen, provide the revocation ticket and click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Upload</span>.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"mko1665702747232__li_d29729e1_d29730e1_d29731e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">This updates the revocation related records on the EMS portal.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529961\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529961\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Returning Standalone On-Premises Served Licenses Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 03, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Returning Standalone On-Premises Served Licenses If you have a standalone on-premises served license that is no longer required, you can return it using the license revocation tool to disable the license file. To revoke a license, you will need the Revocation Tool provided in the /common/bin directory of your Uniface installation as well as in the RMS installation package. This is a Java-based tool that can be run on any platform. To revoke a license: Open the /common/bin directory and double-click the Sentinel RMS Revocation Tool.jar file. You can also run the tool from the command line using the command: C:/Program Files/Uniface/Uniface 10/common/jre/bin/java.exe\" –jar “Sentinel RMS Revocation Tool.jar” Copy Note: Update the file path to match your Uniface installation. When prompted, choose between: Revoke Immediately—perform instant revocation Manual Revoke—perform a step-by-step process for revocation If you select Revoke Immediately , enter your user input values (Product Key, Entitlement ID, or Username) and license information (Activation ID, License File, or License String) when prompted. The complete revocation is performed immediately and revocation related records are automatically updated on the EMS portal. If you select Manual Revoke , on the Generate Permission Ticket screen, enter your login and license information and click Generate . This generates a permission ticket. On the Perform Revocation screen, provide the permission ticket and click Revoke . Choose a file name and location to save the generated revocation ticket. On the Upload Revocation Ticket screen, provide the revocation ticket and click Upload . This updates the revocation related records on the EMS portal. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}